<h2>Key Technical Features</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Database Integration:</strong> Uses MySQL with DBIx::Class for robust data management</li>
    <li><strong>Authentication & Authorization:</strong> Role-based access control system</li>
    <li><strong>Template System:</strong> Template Toolkit for flexible view rendering</li>
    <li><strong>Logging System:</strong> Comprehensive logging for debugging and auditing</li>
    <li><strong>API Integration:</strong> Support for external service integration</li>
</ul>

<h2>User Types and Access Levels</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Administrators:</strong> Full system access and configuration capabilities</li>
    <li><strong>Domain Managers:</strong> Management of specific domain settings and users</li>
    <li><strong>Content Editors:</strong> Content creation and modification privileges</li>
    <li><strong>Regular Users:</strong> Access to domain-specific features</li>
    <li><strong>API Users:</strong> Programmatic access to specific functionalities</li>
    <li><strong>Guests:</strong> Limited access to public content</li>
</ul>
